<title>USA: Pure Atria buys Integrity QA for $43 mln.</title>
<headline>Pure Atria buys Integrity QA for $43 mln.</headline>
<dateline>SUNNYVALE, Calif. 1996-11-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pure Atria said Monday it had agreed to acquire Integrity QA Software, a privately-held company, in a deal valued at about $43 million.</p>
<p>Pure Atria said it will pay $30 million in common stock and $13 million in cash for Integrity.</p>
<p>It said it expects to record a one-time charge of about $48 million to write off in-process research and development and other costs. The deal should close within the next 60 days, it said.</p>
<p>Integrity, of Campbell, Calif., is developing technology to automatically detect software defects.</p>
